   {\n      \"repo\": \"envoyproxy/envoy\",\n      \"path\": \"source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc\",\n      \"symbol\": \"ConnPoolImplBase::tryCreateNewConnection\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The upstream connection pool overflow state is defined in envoy/common/conn_pool.h at lines 96-105, where the PoolFailureReason enum declares the Overflow value with the comment 'A resource overflowed and policy prevented a new connection from being created.'\\n\\nThe overflow condition is emitted and handled primarily in source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc, the base implementation class for all connection pools:\\n\\n1. In ConnPoolImplBase::tryCreateNewConnection (line 128-164): When attempting to create a new connection, if host_->canCreateConnection(priority_) returns false (due to circuit breaker limits), the method increments upstream_cx_overflow_ counter (line 138) to track when connections are prevented from being created.\\n\\n2. In ConnPoolImplBase::attachStreamToClient (line 166-211): When attaching a stream to a client connection, if enforceMaxRequests() is true and the resource manager's requests().canCreate() returns false (line 175), indicating max concurrent requests per connection is exceeded, the method calls onPoolFailure() with PoolFailureReason::Overflow (line 177-178) and increments upstream_rq_pending_overflow_ counter (line 179).\\n\\n3. In ConnPoolImplBase::newStreamImpl (line 255-314): When creating a new pending stream, if the resource manager's pendingRequests().canCreate() returns false (line 282), indicating the pending request limit is exceeded, the method calls onPoolFailure() with PoolFailureReason::Overflow (line 284) and increments upstream_rq_pending_overflow_ counter (line 286). The debug log message 'max pending streams overflow' (line 283) indicates this condition.\\n\\nAdditionally, in source/common/upstream/conn_pool_map_impl.h at line 38, the ConnPoolMap<>::getPool method increments upstream_cx_pool_overflow_ when unable to create a new connection pool due to resource limits exceeded.\\n\\nThe traffic statistics counters are defined in envoy/upstream/upstream.h:\\n- upstream_cx_overflow_: Tracks when connections are prevented by circuit breaker limits\\n- upstream_cx_pool_overflow_: Tracks when connection pool creation is prevented\\n- upstream_rq_pending_overflow_: Tracks when pending or concurrent request limits are exceeded\\n\\nAll overflow handling routes through the PoolFailureReason::Overflow enum state, providing a unified mechanism for tracking resource exhaustion events across the connection pool hierarchy.\"\n}\n",
