          "text": "Perfect! I've completed the analysis of the Envoy codebase and found the C++ source files that define and handle the upstream connection pool overflow condition. Here's a summary of my findings:\n\n## Key Findings\n\n### 1. **Overflow State Definition**\n- **File**: `envoy/common/conn_pool.h` (lines 96-105)\n- **Symbol**: `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` enum\n- Defines the overflow condition as: \"A resource overflowed and policy prevented a new connection from being created.\"\n\n### 2. **Overflow Emission & Handling**\nThe main implementation is in `source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc`:\n\n**Three main overflow triggers:**\n\n1. **Connection Creation Overflow** (line 138)\n   - When `host_->canCreateConnection()` returns false\n   - Increments `upstream_cx_overflow_` counter\n\n2. **Max Concurrent Requests Overflow** (lines 175-179)\n   - In `attachStreamToClient()`: When max streams per connection exceeded\n   - Calls `onPoolFailure()` with `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`\n   - Increments `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` counter\n\n3. **Max Pending Requests Overflow** (lines 282-286)\n   - In `newStreamImpl()`: When pending request limit exceeded\n   - Log message: \"max pending streams overflow\"\n   - Calls `onPoolFailure()` with `PoolFailureReason::Overflow`\n   - Increments `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` counter\n\n### 3. **Connection Pool Creation Overflow**\n- **File**: `source/common/upstream/conn_pool_map_impl.h` (line 38)\n- Increments `upstream_cx_pool_overflow_` when unable to create a new connection pool\n\n### 4. **Counter Definitions**\n- **File**: `envoy/upstream/upstream.h`\n- Defines traffic stats: `upstream_cx_overflow_`, `upstream_cx_pool_overflow_`, `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_`\n\nThe complete analysis has been saved to `/workspace/answer.json`.",
